<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10417> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10417" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/27> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "MRR identifies C. Octavius, who joined the Liberators on the Capitol on the Ides of March and despite not having taken part in the assassination of Caesar later claimed to have taken part, with the elder C. Octavius Balbus who was caught and executed as a proscriptus in Rome. However Hinard doubts that such a notorious celebrant of Caesar's death would still be in Rome as late as November 43, and judges C. Octavius and C. Octavius Balbus separate people." .
